# Profile System

The Profile system represents the user's identity inside LexMastery.

It is both personal and academic.

---

# Product Vision

Profile must:

- represent learner identity
- store learning preferences
- show performance summary
- manage jurisdiction settings
- support personalization engine

---

# Architecture

Presentation Layer

↓

ProfileController (Riverpod)

↓

ProfileState

↓

ProfileRepository

↓

User Service API

---

# State Management

ProfileState includes:

- loading
- loaded
- updating
- error

Core Data:

- userInfo
- jurisdiction
- examType
- learningGoals
- preferences
- progressSummary

---

# Profile Data

Includes:

- name
- email
- avatar
- study goal
- exam target
- experience level

---

# Jurisdiction Settings

Critical for legal context:

- country
- legal system type
- exam board
- curriculum alignment

---

# Learning Preferences

- study pace
- difficulty preference
- AI assistance level
- notification intensity

---

# Navigation Rules

Profile is accessible from:

- Dashboard
- Settings
- AI Tutor
- Progress

---

# Offline Behaviour

- view profile offline
- edit requires sync
- cached preferences available

---

# API Contracts

GET /profile

PUT /profile/update

GET /profile/preferences

POST /profile/sync

---

# Analytics Events

profile_view

profile_update

jurisdiction_changed

learning_goal_updated

---

# UI Composition Rules

Profile UI must include:

- identity header
- progress summary
- preference settings
- jurisdiction selector
- edit mode

---

# UX Rules

- changes must be simple and reversible
- avoid deep nested settings
- prioritize clarity

---

# Error Handling

- preserve local edits
- retry sync safely

---

# Performance

- profile load <200ms
- updates must be instant locally

---

# Accessibility

Must support:

- screen reader labels
- editable field navigation
- high contrast mode

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

Profile update logic

Preference handling

Jurisdiction mapping

Widget Tests:

Profile screen

Edit forms

Summary widgets

Integration Tests:

Profile sync flow

Preference update flow

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating profile features:

- always treat jurisdiction as core data
- always support offline edits
- always sync safely
- never overwrite user preferences without confirmation